OL,7,GBodgeham-on-Wye is a village and civil
OL,8,Gparish, in Herefordshire, England,
OL,9,Gnear the border with Wales. It has
OL,10,Gexhibited rapid growth, more than
OL,11,Gdoubling in size since 2024[1], with a
OL,12,G2026 population of 30. It lies in the
OL,13,Gsouth-east of the county, on the River
OL,14,GWye[citation needed], and adjacent to
OL,15,Gthe Eastnor Deer Park. Bodgeham-on-Wye
OL,16,Gis upside-down.
